, how the idea of "shared values" obscures debate, and how tolerating religious differences simply isn't enough to guarantee equality. Reasonable Accommodation provides a much-needed critical assessment of this phrase and theorizes religious diversity and freedom of religion beyond the meaning of "tolerance" as it sometimes implies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aRELIGION / Religion, Politics & State.2bisacsh1 aBakht, Natasha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeaman, Lori G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeaman, Lori G., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBeckford, James A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeyer, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBouma, Gary D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEisenberg, Avigail, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLefebvre, Solange, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRiis, Ole, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShipley, Heather, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2012z978311127413308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2012z978311127716508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311141860540uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077482277040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774822770423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774822770/original  a978-3-11-127413-3  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2012b2012  a978-3-11-127716-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Packag